		<img width="2500" height="1200" src="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-reef-restoration.jpg" class="singlepostthumb wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" srcset="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-reef-restoration.jpg 2500w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-reef-restoration-520x250.jpg 520w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-reef-restoration-1200x576.jpg 1200w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-reef-restoration-768x369.jpg 768w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-reef-restoration-1536x737.jpg 1536w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-reef-restoration-2048x983.jpg 2048w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-reef-restoration-900x432.jpg 900w" sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" /><div class="post-thumbnail-caption">As a newly restored oyster reef grows in Adelaide, Australia, it‚Äôs creating habitat for a bevy of species. Photo courtesy of Stefan Andrews</div>
			<article class="main container col4">
								<header class="maincol">
										<h1 class="pagetitle">The Australian Oyster Reef Revival</h1>
										<h2 class="dek singlepagecontainer">A successful restoration project on the Adelaide coast is raising hopes for the future of a long-lost ecosystem.</h2>
										<section class="singlebyline singlepagecontainer">
						<h3 class="invis">Authored by</h3>
						by  
										<a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/profiles/gennaro-tomma/" class="tagmanager" id="author_link_top" >Gennaro Tomma</a>								<br/>
												</section>
					 
					<aside class="singlebydatewords singlepagecontainer">
						<h3 class="invis">Wordcount</h3>
						September 26, 2024 | 700 words, about 3 minutes
					</aside>

					
				</header>

				
				<aside class="social-sharing">

